Rating: 3
I made this last nite and thought it was awesome. It was so easy to make and had such good flavors. It is a good summer pasta dish. I used about double the amount of basil from my garden, but didn't use the whole 6 oz container of feta. I sauteed the shrimp with garlic and olive oil and then added the marinade (minus the feta) to make a warm sauce. I grated two cloves of garlic for the marinade and used the other two for the shrimps. Add the feta as you toss the pasta with the sauce so it melts a little and adds a bit of creaminess to it. I would like to try the non-cooked sauce next time with my yellow and roma tomatoes. I brought the leftovers to work for lunch and it reheated very well.

